  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nFor test purpose, I deliberately included a invalid BLS signature in the deposit data and submitted the transaction to ETH1 deposit contract. Then I got the \"invalid\" deposit on ETH2. \r\n\r\nI previously sent a valid deposit so the validator is awaiting activation. But the explorer shows The current balance, effective balance and deposits received are all 32ETH. The invalid deposit of 32ETH was burned on ETH1 but considered \"invalid\" on ETH2. So does it mean the 32ETH was not transferred successfully to ETH2? Does this mean I forever lost this 32ETH? Is there any way to retrieve them on ETH1? Or maybe I can retrieve them once the transfer function launches on ETH2?\r\n\r\nAppreciate any help. Thanks.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20232539/93443915-01e19300-f903-11ea-9e64-bc3eea15a41a.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20232539/93443833-fd1cdf00-f902-11ea-9871-81fe9f722ff5.png)\r\n",
